Ready to deepen your AI skills and transform your career? Enroll in one of 
our final AI courses of the year! Courses from Stanford Online offer access 
to the deep expertise and cutting-edge insights of renowned Stanford 
faculty in a flexible format for working professionals.  


Machine Learning with Graphs | November 6 - January 28, 2024


      * Explore computational, algorithmic, and modeling challenges
        specific to the analysis of graphs.


      * Leverage state-of-the-art graph neural networks to make better
        predictions over graph structured data.


      * Master the mechanics of PyTorch Geometric (the leading python
        library for Machine Learning with Graphs) to build your own graph
        neural networks.


      * Learn to identify recurrent and significant patterns of
        interconnection in real-world data though network motifs, subgraph
        algorithms, and graph-based recommender systems.


Learn more >>
<https://eventing.coursera..vn1t3vEJUORKZ04fKiYbKUZlA8qsPBX6n90Sgr1Lj2o>


 


Reinforcement Learning | November 13 - February 4, 2024


      * Gain a solid introduction to the field of reinforcement learning
        and learn about the core approaches and challenges in the field,
        including generalization and exploration


      * Design and implement RL algorithms on a large scale with linear
        value function approximation and deep RL techniques.


      * Model and optimize your strategies with policy-based RL such as
        score functions, policy gradient, and REINFORCE.


      * Evaluate and enhance your RL algorithms with bandits and MDPs.


      * Maximize learnings from static datasets using offline and batch RL
        methods.

 About the internship

 Selected intern's day-to-day responsibilities include: 1. Brainstorming and
preparing plans of action to tackle business problems 2. Preparing official
documents containing questions that need to be answered (prepare the list of
topics to be answered, brainstorm answers, and craft the final draft) 3.
Studying the internal workflows of the different departments to determine
the best way to minimize the time spent on each internal step, and testing
the model 4. Documenting key insights you collect in proper formats and
software requested by the organization 5. Understanding the business
operation to a micro level and fine-tuning the systems and processes to make
it seamless 6. Conducting surveys through Google Forms and creating reports
7. Educating yourself about what your task requires through extensive
research online 8. Assisting leadership with making key decisions Note: We
will never call you and ask you for money to register for this internship.

 About Ozibook Tech Solutions Private Limited

 Ozibook is a tech startup (based out in Bangalore, India) that focuses on
building products that improve the quality of living for you and your
family. As a part of our vision, the first product we are building is in the
field of education called Ozigen - a social learning platform, where we help
educational content creators power their knowledge online and connect
students with teachers who they want to learn from through live classes or
subscription for their content and community. If the concept of making the
education system better and being a part of a tech startup excites you, then
do apply to us.

 About the internship

 As a backend development intern at ADM Education & Welfare Society, you
will have the opportunity to work on exciting projects that make a positive
impact on the education sector. You will collaborate with a talented team of
developers to build and maintain the backend infrastructure of our platform,
ensuring seamless functionality for users. Your creativity and
problem-solving skills will be put to the test as you tackle challenging
tasks and contribute to the overall success of the organization. Selected
intern's day-to-day responsibilities include: 1. Assist in developing and
maintaining backend applications using programming languages such as Python,
Java, or Node.js 2. Collaborate with the front-end development team to
integrate user-facing elements with server-side logic 3. Write clean,
efficient, and secure code that meets industry standards and best practices
4. Participate in code reviews to ensure quality and consistency across
projects 5. Troubleshoot and debug issues to optimize performance and
enhance user experience 6. Stay up-to-date on emerging technologies and
trends in backend development 7. Contribute ideas and solutions to enhance
the overall functionality and scalability of the platform If you are a
passionate and driven individual looking to gain hands-on experience in
backend development, this internship is the perfect opportunity for you to
grow and learn in a supportive and dynamic environment. Join us in making a
difference in the world of education!



 About ADM EDUCATION & WELFARE SOCIETY

 We, as an organization are known for providing computer and vocational
education in rural areas with economic costing through a strong network of
centers in small villages and towns. We are providing education, which is
required in every step of life, age, and workplace. Our well-trained staff
is ready to teach such a practical education, which is needed by a student,
housewife, businessman, retired person, employee, self-employed, farmer,
uneducated person, etc. We are generating employment opportunities for
trained and skilled people who do not have a formal school certificate. We
are also running courses to empower unskilled women for their economic and
social upliftment.

          and R.

When you join the Postgraduate Diploma in Applied Statistics
<https://eventing.coursera.-MjAyNC0wMy0wNCIsImNhbXBhaWduR3JvdXAiOiJRNWxqSU5xc0VlNkE3NFc3akVWS0JBIiwibGlua3MiOltdfX0sInVzZXJJZCI6MTMwODYwMDE1fQ.eBa8DAmwoV_0_22higd3B_tWT6xmLPk75PnVOKQLmkU> 
, you will learn advanced statistical techniques and predictive models 
required to make data-driven decisions and advance your career in data 
science. You can immediately apply many of the skills that you will learn 
at your current workplace.
You will learn from a leading institution that influences policy decisions, 
work on real-world data from public projects, and develop important skills 
from industry experts.

Explore the unique features of the program :


        * Learn from industry experts : Interact in weekly live sessions
          with renowned scientists and develop industry-ready skills from
          accomplished experts with 25+ years of experience.

        * Access career readiness support : Take part in specially
          organised industry speaker sessions, career workshops and
          interact in 1-1 sessions with global mentors.

        * Join an elite student community and prestigious alumni network : 
          Learners include senior professionals with an average experience
          of 12 years at organisations like Microsoft, IBM, Accenture, EY,
          etc. and are from 15+ countries.

        * Access potential job opportunities facilitated by ISI : Through
          the placement committee led by an ISI faculty convenor, you will
          showcase your skills to prospective employers. There is no
          placement guarantee offered by ISI.

        * Attend the official convocation ceremony : Receive the
          certificate hard-copy issued directly by ISI during the
          graduation ceremony along with the on-campus students.

        * Set you own pace : Complete your studies in up to 36 months at no
          additional cost - focus on your academic pursuits without
          compromising on your other commitments.

DeepLearning.AI has expanded its course catalog with new offerings that 
cover practical areas such as agentic AI, function-calling and data 
extraction, and carbon-aware computing practices.


Explore our new courses for free: 


AI Agents in LangGraph


LangChain, a popular open source framework for building LLM applications, 
recently introduced LangGraph. This extension allows developers to create 
highly controllable agents.


In AI Agents in LangGraph
<https://eventing.coursera..WMhpw_wz4gV8P0luccHCylsAvgSToNsLZSDQHY7huiE> 
you will learn to build an agent from scratch using Python and an LLM, and 
then rebuild it using LangGraph to learn its components and how to combine 
them to build flow-based applications.

using natural language, simplifying the process for querying and extracting 
insights.


Building Your Own Database Agent
<https://eventing.coursera..ZI9wT90S91nLuPvHnxGapUeUj0hAFuu4UyQjmELg1Xw>

more sophisticated interaction with their databases through natural

Function-Calling and Data Extraction with LLMs


This course will teach you two critical skills for building applications 
with LLMs: function-calling and structured data extraction.


Function-calling allows you to extend LLMs with custom capabilities by 
enabling them to form calls to external functions based on natural language 
instructions. Structured data extraction enables LLMs to pull usable 
information from unstructured text.


In Function-Calling and Data Extraction
<https://eventing.coursera..M43F8urC2pqhmMPZ31o7yg2wIe1szxy4LztVvH8LcdU>

tasks, and has 13 billion parameters so it can be hosted locally.

The Master of Science in Computer Science
<https://eventing.coursera..8iBuKBaxQ5ocKlIpNbS8TpBtKAKChw9j7_BQxSJaWow> 
on Coursera emphasizes job-relevant subjects and applications with 
coursework reflecting fast-changing developments in the computer science 
field. You will graduate with practical, up-to-date knowledge essential for 
success, including an advanced understanding of modern computer science 
topics like algorithms, AI/machine learning, systems, ethics, and 
computing.

US-based graduates from the CU Boulder MS-CS on-campus program work for 
giants like Google, Microsoft, Amazon, Facebook, Adobe, Lockheed-Martin, 
IBM, Salesforce, and Accenture, as well as start-up companies of all sizes. 
Popular sectors include information technology, aerospace, finance, 
manufacturing, consulting, and government laboratories.

Did you know? The U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics expects employment of 
computer and information research scientists to grow 21 percent from 2021 
to 2031, much faster than the average for all occupations.

Dear zakie khan,


Developing your skills in AI today will help you stay ahead of the curve 
and unlock your potential. Understanding how it works, how to use it, and 
especially how to build with it puts you in the driver's seat!


Generative AI for Everyone
<https://eventing.coursera.org/redirectSigned/eyJrZXkiOiJlbWFpbC5saW5rLm9wZW4iLCJ2YWx1ZSI6eyJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5jb3Vyc2VyYS5vcmcvbGVhcm4vZ2VuZXJhdGl2ZS1haS1mb3ItZXZlcnlvbmU_.XU3hIC4UUo44t3ZRx-lf0ltfWN4MNCfZ7Rj05wA5auA>


Instructed by Andrew Ng, Generative AI for Everyone course offers his 
unique perspective on empowering you and your work with generative AI. 
Andrew will guide you through how generative AI works and what it can (and 
can't) do. It includes hands-on exercises where you'll learn to use 
generative AI to help in day-to-day work and receive tips on effective 
prompt engineering, as well as learning how to go beyond prompting for more 
advanced uses of AI. This is for anyone looking for non-technical primer in 
getting started with generative AI!


Generative AI with LLMs
<https://eventing.coursera.org/redirectSigned/eyJrZXkiOiJlbWFpbC5saW5rLm9wZW4iLCJ2YWx1ZSI6eyJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5jb3Vyc2VyYS5vcmcvbGVhcm4vZ2VuZXJhdGl2ZS1haS13aXRoLWxsbXM_.-z2ZCtwtxXRNNluAcutMlcIZX0ReRZVpBlp7gGDRvBQ>


In Generative AI with LLMs, you'll learn the fundamentals of generative AI 
and how to deploy it in real-world applications. You'll also gain a 
functional understanding of how generative AI functions at a technical 
level, and receive instruction from expert AWS AI builders who actively 
build and deploy AI in business use cases. This course is for those looking 
for technical foundations in building and applying generative AI.


Mathematics for Machine Learning and Data Science
<https://eventing.coursera.org/redirectSigned/eyJrZXkiOiJlbWFpbC5saW5rLm9wZW4iLCJ2YWx1ZSI6eyJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5jb3Vyc2VyYS5vcmcvc3BlY2lhbGl6YXRpb25zL21hdGhlbWF0aWNzLWZvci1tYWNoaW5lLWxlYXJuaW5nLWFuZC1kYXRhLXNjaWVuY2U_.sQJPFYg5h5xF68f7VKrPS0Q8wVAMaQf2yqxI3QfiRHw>


Mathematics for Machine Learning and Data Science will give you a deep 
understanding of the mathematics behind AI, including calculus, linear 
algebra, statistics, and probability. You'll also learn statistical 
techniques that will empower you to get more out of your data analysis and 
help you ace machine learning interview questions. This specialization is 
for anyone wanting to build a foundation of mathematical skills for use in 
a career in machine learning and data science!


Keep learning,


The DeepLearning.AI team

from industry experts.

Explore the unique features of the program :


        * Learn from industry experts : Interact in weekly live sessions
          with renowned scientists and develop industry-ready skills from
          accomplished experts with 25+ years of experience.

        * Access career readiness support : Take part in specially
          organised industry speaker sessions, career workshops and
          interact in 1-1 sessions with global mentors.

        * Join an elite student community and prestigious alumni network : 
          Learners include senior professionals with an average experience
          of 12 years at organisations like Microsoft, IBM, Accenture, EY,
          etc. and are from 15+ countries.

        * Access potential job opportunities facilitated by ISI : 
          Placements are a student-driven activity led by an ISI faculty
          convenor - there is no placement guarantee offered by ISI.

        * Attend the official convocation ceremony : Receive the
          certificate hard-copy issued directly by ISI during the
          graduation ceremony along with the on-campus students.

        * Set you own pace : Complete your studies in up to 36 months at no
          additional cost - focus on your academic pursuits without
          compromising on your other commitments.

undercurrents, such as security, data management, DataOps, data

        analytics and machine learning use cases.

The Master of Science in Information Technology (MSIT) is a 2 year degree 
programme by IIIT Hyderabad. It is modelled on an existing on-campus 
programme that has successfully launched technology careers for over 20 
years!

The programme equips you with foundational computer science principles and 
allows you build expertise in one of three in-demand sub domains.

What can you expect:


        * Choose your specialisation: Choose from three key digital
          technology paths in Year 2- full stack development, data science
          or machine learning/artificial intelligence.

        * Experience 'learning by doing': You will learn through theory and
          applied projects in university specialisation courses. You will
          also experience a capstone project in Term 8, like building a
          social media platform or a multilingual voice assistant.

        * Avail optional industry certificate courses: You can pursue
          mapped IBM & Meta paid courses. Completing this courses and
          passing a IIIT-H assessment may grant you course credits, and
          also give a unique edge to your learning and portfolio.

        * Pursue relevant career options: Upon completing the programme,
          you will be qualified to pursue career roles such as a software
          developer, ML engineer, data scientist and much more.


Classes start in July 2024. Start your application today!

The Master of Science in Information Technology (MSIT) is a 2 year degree 
programme by IIIT Hyderabad, one of the top ranked engineering institutes 
in India.

The programme equips you with core computer science principles such as 
programming, algorithms, data structures and further build expertise in one 
of three IT domains from scratch.

Why should you consider applying?


        * Modelled on a proven programme: The institute's on-campus MSIT
          programme has launched technology careers for over 20 years, with
          its past alumni recruited by top IT firms like Amazon, Microsoft
          and IBM.

        * Three in-demand specialisations: Explore three specialisation
          paths- full stack development, data science and machine
          learning/artificial intelligence.

        * Industry-relevant learning: Prepare yourself for industry roles
          through expert masterclasses, mentorship, and optional industry
          certificate courses from Meta and IBM.

        * 'Learning by doing' methodology: Experience applied learning
          through 20+ projects, virtual lab work, essential tools and a 12
          week capstone project.

As Andrew Ng recently noted, "AI agent workflows will drive massive AI 
progress this year â€” perhaps even more than the next generation of 
foundation models." 


In line with this pivotal trend, weâ€™ve launched a series of short courses 
to help you build and implement AI agents through hands-on lessons, while 
gaining experience with leading frameworks like crewAI, AutoGen, and 
LangGraph. Many of these are beginner friendly, with just basic Python as a 
prerequisite recommendation. Check out our available short courses on AI 
agents!


Multi AI Agent Systems with crewAI


Taught by JoÃ£o Moura, founder and CEO of crewAI, Multi AI Agent Systems 
with crewAI
<https://eventing.coursera..3JlwLyvRENs4fAmCZEUDh-mH8WsjaIL40F6sTcojunc> 
will teach you key components of AI agents, and how to assign specialized 
roles to agents and coordinate their efforts for optimal performance.


With crewAI, an open source library for building multi-agent systems, 
you'll get hands-on experience building agent crews for processes like 
tailoring resumes and interview prep for job applications, researching, 
writing, and editing technical articles, conducting customer outreach 
campaigns and financial analysis, planning events, and more.


Youâ€™ll design and prompt a team of agents through natural language to 
automate your business workflows, exceeding the performance of prompting a 
single LLM.


Enroll for free
<https://eventing.coursera..3JlwLyvRENs4fAmCZEUDh-mH8WsjaIL40F6sTcojunc>


AI Agents in LangGraph


LangGraph allows developers to create highly controllable agents.


In AI Agents in LangGraph
<https://eventing.coursera..yBwU8sb-8bUh2mHAjwPDh7gUQCiaXvGTMH2zSy4-XH4> 
 you will learn to build an agent from scratch using Python and an LLM, and 
then you will rebuild it using LangGraph, learning about its components and 
how to combine them to build flow-based applications.


Additionally, you will learn about agentic search, which returns multiple 
answers in an agent-friendly format, enhancing the agentâ€™s built-in 
knowledge. This course will show you how to use agentic search in your 
applications to provide better data for agents to enhance their output.


Enroll for free
<https://eventing.coursera..yBwU8sb-8bUh2mHAjwPDh7gUQCiaXvGTMH2zSy4-XH4>


Building Agentic RAG with LlamaIndex


In this course made in collaboration with LlamaIndex and taught by its 
co-founder and CEO, Jerry Liu, you'll build agents capable of intelligently 
navigating, summarizing, and comparing information across multiple research 
papers from arXiv, and learn how to debug these agents, ensuring you can 
guide their actions effectively.


Unlike the standard retrieval augmented generation (RAG) pipelineâ€”suitable 
for simple queries across a few documentsâ€”agentic RAG adapts based on 
initial findings to enhance further data retrieval. In Building Agentic RAG 
with LlamaIndex
<https://eventing.coursera..D7GwOavEJVdoWl700Krp0DQqQM3QXF9LcM2ZU4DihmE> 
, you'll use this framework to build research agents skilled in tool use, 
reasoning, and decision-making with your data.

AI Agentic Design Patterns with AutoGen 


This short course was made in collaboration with Microsoft and Penn State 
University, and is taught by AutoGen creators Chi Wang, Principal 
Researcher at Microsoft Research, and Qingyun Wu, Assistant Professor at

In AI Agentic Design Patterns with AutoGen
<https://eventing.coursera..cnBFZwu18oWYfTJFNxgtdNqWuz--e_VzmeA1Rwz6L5A> 
, youâ€™ll learn how to build and customize multi-agent systems, enabling 
agents to take on different roles and collaborate to accomplish complex 
tasks using AutoGen, a framework that enables the development of LLM 
applications using multi-agents, all while implementing four agentic design 
patterns: Reflection, Tool use, Planning, and Multi-agent collaboration 
using AutoGen.

Ready to develop your AI skills and transform your career? Courses from 
Stanford Online offer access to the deep expertise and cutting-edge 
insights of renowned Stanford faculty in a flexible format for working 
professionals.


Artificial Intelligence: Principles & Techniques | October 2 - December 10, 
2023


Considering a pivot to Artificial Intelligence? This course is the perfect 
jumping-off point. In this rigorous, graduate-level course you will:


      * Gain a broad overview of the modern AI landscape, including machine
        learning, state-based models, variable-based models, and logic.


      * Learn how machines can engage in problem-solving, reasoning,
        learning, and interaction as you design, test, and implement new
        algorithms.


By the end of the 10-week course, you will have the confidence and skills 
to analyze and solve new AI problems you encounter in your career.

Are you a healthcare professional looking to advance your skills, or are 
you passionate about increasing your personal health and wellness 
expertise? 


From executives to team leaders to individual learners at home, Stanford 
Online offers a variety of courses and programs
<https://eventing.coursera._.1nU4RuwSb26BKYax_Isfz7V5vFlJIgHcq3xePc2HhTE> 
designed to fit your learning goals, budget, and schedule. Each of our 
online courses is taught by renowned Stanford faculty, covering a wide 
range of topics, including genetics, biomedical data science, AI in 
healthcare, nutrition, epidemiology, addiction and more.

Course - Digital Health Product Development


Dive into the world of health innovation and learn how technologies like 
telehealth and wearables are ideated, developed, and brought to market. Add 
skills like concept generation and needs finding to your resume.
